# Git Conventions

## Branch Naming

- **main** — Staging branch (default). Protected; integrate via PRs.
- **feature/[name]** — New features (e.g. `feature/auth`, `feature/user-dashboard`).
- **fix/[name]** — Bug fixes and debug sessions (e.g. `fix/login-redirect`, `fix/hydration`).
- **refactor/[name]** — Config changes, AI rules, setup, non-feature refactors (e.g. `refactor/biome-config`, `refactor/cursor-rules`).
- **docs/[name]** — Documentation (e.g. `docs/brand-guideline.md`).
- **other/[name]** — Anything that doesn’t fit above (e.g.`other/chore-deps`).

Use lowercase, short descriptive names. Prefer hyphens for multi-word names.

## Commit Message Format

Match the branch type as the prefix, then a short description:

```
<type> - <description>
```

Examples:

- `feature - add login form and validation`
- `fix - resolve hydration mismatch on theme toggle`
- `refactor - add tailwind guardrail rule`
- `docs - update README`
- `other - upgrade deps & libs`

Keep the description in lowercase (except proper nouns), concise, and in present tense (“add” not “added”). No period at the end.

## Summary

| Branch prefix | Use for              | Commit example                    |
|---------------|----------------------|-----------------------------------|
| feature/      | New features         | `feature - add user profile page` |
| fix/          | Bugs / debug         | `fix - correct modal focus trap`  |
| refactor/     | Config, rules, setup | `refactor - extend biome config`  |
| docs/         | Documentation        | `docs - update README.md`         |
| other/        | Everything else      | `other - bump dependencies`       |
